<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9622> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9622" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 430" ;
	dprr:hasID 9622 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7064> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7064" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Usually considered the elder son of the consul of 70. Praefectus equitum, 58, perhaps 57-56. In MRR 2.199, refer also to J. Suolahti, Junior Officers 216, 292. In MRR 2.204, refer to Caes. BG 3.21.2. Quaestor 55? Sydenham (CRR 155) dates his SC coinage to 54, but H. B. Mattingly attributes it to a quaestorship which he dates in 55, holding that the type refers to his father's part in Sulla's victory and that he gave the Ludi Victoriae Sullanae at Praeneste as quaestor urbanus (NC 16, 1956, 20f.). While this seems doubtful, note that Crawford dates the coinage and the quaestorship to 55 (RRC 1.454, no. 430). See Sumner, Orators 149-150. Syme, however, has shown that the balance of evidence favors considering that Marcus was the elder son, and raises further doubt that Publius was a quaestor when he issued his coinage or that he was a quaestorius when he joined his father in Syria (Latomus 39, 1980, 403-408-RP 3.1220-1225).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7064 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5318> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5318" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Died this year at Carrhae (see above, Legates). Succeeded by M. Tullius Cicero." ;
	dprr:hasID 5318 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5297> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5297" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served with his father against the Parthians and fell in battle near Carrhae (Plut. Crass. 23.4-5; 25-26; Dio 40.21.2-22.1; cf. Cic. Brut. 281-282; Div. 2.22; Fam. 13.16; Liv. Per. 106; Ovid Fasti 5.583-584; 6.465-469; Ars Amat. 1.179; Prop. 2.10.14; 3.4.9; Val. Max. 1.6.11; Plut. Pomp. 55.1, and 74.3; App. BC 2.18; Flor. 1.46.10; Iustin 42.4.4; Dio 41.55.3; Sid. Apoll. Carm. 2.454f.; 7.100; 9.251; Eutrop. 6.18.1; Jerome Chr. ad ann. 56, p. 155 Helm; Oros. 6.13.3)." ;
	dprr:hasID 5297 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5259> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5259" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Joined his father in Syria in the winter of 54-53 with 1000 Gallic horse (Plut. Crass. 17.4 and 6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 5259 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5215> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5215" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. Cic. 36.1. Probably successor of L. Licinius Lucullus; see 56, Augurs, cf. Dio 39.17." ;
	dprr:hasID 5215 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5192> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5192" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Issued coins, perhaps as a Quaestor (Mommsen, RMW 640f., no. 288; Grueber, CRRB.M 1.487f.; see Pink, p. 39)." ;
	dprr:hasID 5192 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5161> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5161" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Aquitania by Caesar, where he carried through a very successful campaign (Caes. BG 3.11, 20-27; cf. 8.46.1; Dio 39.46; Oros. 6.8.19-22; and on his title, Dio 39.31). Returned to Rome with veterans to support the candidacy of Pompey and Crassus for the consulship of 55 (Dio 39.31.2; cf. Cic. QF 2.7.2). See 57, Legates." ;
	dprr:hasID 5161 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5103> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5103" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Caesar in Gaul, at times in command of a legion (Caes. BG 2.34; cf. on his title, Dio 39.31.2, #). Wintered in western Gaul (Caes. BG 3.7-9; Oros. 6.8.7). Willems (1.536) holds that Dio erroneously terms him a Legate, when he had not yet held the quaestorship." ;
	dprr:hasID 5103 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5066> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5066" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In command of cavalry against Ariovistus (Caes. BG 1.52.7)." ;
	dprr:hasID 5066 .
